## Topology Mirror

Mirror the runtime registry here for operator visibility. If this differs from
`~/turtleos/mage_registry.yaml`, the registry wins and this file should be updated.

| Practitioner/Space | practice_root | workshop_root | runtime_root |
|--------------------|---------------|---------------|--------------|
| primary | `~/workshops/<mage>` | *(none)* | `~/workshops/<mage>` |

Rules:
- `practice_root` is the only writable daily practice root.
- `workshop_root` is optional and read-mostly; use it when a Mage brings a full Magic workshop.
- `runtime_root` is Turtle-local operational state: thread-state, readiness, caches, locks.
- A practitioner must never have two writable practice roots.

## Spirit Ops (Via SSH)

Use these templates when alias-aware tooling is unavailable.

```bash
ssh turtle@<tailscale-ip> '~/turtleos/venv/bin/python3 ~/turtleos/spirit_ops.py send <channel-id> "message"'
ssh turtle@<tailscale-ip> '~/turtleos/venv/bin/python3 ~/turtleos/spirit_ops.py read <channel-id> 20'
ssh turtle@<tailscale-ip> '~/turtleos/venv/bin/python3 ~/turtleos/spirit_ops.py threads <channel-id>'
ssh turtle@<tailscale-ip> '~/turtleos/venv/bin/python3 ~/turtleos/spirit_ops.py thread <channel-id> "thread name"'
```

